12
The Board issues licenses to new applicants by examination or by license transfer.
Individuals requesting licensure by examination must submit evidence of completion of an internship, graduation from an educational institution of pharmacy approved by the Board, and successful completion of a Board administered written jurisprudence examination in addition to the national examination.
Persons who produce satisfactory evidence that they have graduated from a school of pharmacy outside of the United States and have passed a foreign graduate equivalency test are eligible to take the national examination.
Applicants for licensure by transfer are required to submit their documentation to a Board designated clearinghouse for review.
