The Board has a variety of enforcement mechanisms available created by statute.
The Board may take disciplinary action by denying, suspending, refusing to renew or reinstate, or revoking a license.
The Board may also issue a letter of admonition when an investigation discloses an instance of misconduct that does not warrant more severe disciplinary action by the Board.
The Board also issues confidential letters of concern that are not considered formal disciplinary action.
